# Backend Decision

- Both `Convex` and `MongoDB` are allowed at this stage.
- Do not over-couple the app to one backend until the product workflow is clearer.
- Choose `Convex` when realtime sync, reactive queries, or rapid full-stack iteration are the main need.
- Choose `MongoDB` when document-centric storage, flexible ingestion pipelines, and broader ecosystem control matter more.
- Keep domain models and business logic portable so backend changes stay possible.
- Centralize backend access behind clear server or data-layer boundaries.
- Revisit the backend decision once the ingestion pipeline and user interaction patterns are better defined.
